---
/**
 * Accordion Simple (tanpa button tag)
 * Gaya Neo-Brutalism minimal: klik header (div) untuk toggle konten.
 */
---

<div x-data="{ open: null }" class="space-y-4 max-w-xl mx-auto font-sans">
  <!-- Accordion Item -->
  <div
    class="border-4 border-black rounded-2xl bg-pink-200 shadow-[6px_6px_0_0_#000] cursor-pointer hover:-translate-y-1 active:translate-y-0 duration-150 ease-linear"
    @click="open === 1 ? open = null : open = 1"
  >
    <div
      class="flex justify-between items-center px-6 py-4 font-bold text-black select-none"
    >
      <span>What is Neo-Brutalism?</span>
      <span class="relative flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6">
        <span class="absolute w-4 h-0.5 bg-black"></span>
        <span
          class="absolute h-4 w-0.5 bg-black transition-opacity duration-200"
          :class="open === 1 ? 'opacity-0' : 'opacity-100'"></span>
      </span>
    </div>

    <div
      class="px-6 text-gray-900 text-sm leading-relaxed overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out"
      :class="open === 1 ? 'max-h-40 pb-4' : 'max-h-0 pb-0'"
    >
      Neo-Brutalism combines bold color blocks, thick borders, and unapologetic
      flat shadows — it’s raw, loud, and expressive. Perfect for creative UI
      documentation.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Accordion Item 2 -->
  <div
    class="border-4 border-black rounded-2xl bg-yellow-200 shadow-[6px_6px_0_0_#000] cursor-pointer hover:-translate-y-1 active:translate-y-0 duration-150 ease-linear"
    @click="open === 2 ? open = null : open = 2"
  >
    <div
      class="flex justify-between items-center px-6 py-4 font-bold text-black select-none"
    >
      <span>Why is it popular?</span>
      <span class="relative flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6">
        <span class="absolute w-4 h-0.5 bg-black"></span>
        <span
          class="absolute h-4 w-0.5 bg-black transition-opacity duration-200"
          :class="open === 2 ? 'opacity-0' : 'opacity-100'"></span>
      </span>
    </div>

    <div
      class="px-6 text-gray-900 text-sm leading-relaxed overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out"
      :class="open === 2 ? 'max-h-40 pb-4' : 'max-h-0 pb-0'"
    >
      Because it’s a rebellion against overly polished UIs — it feels real and
      human. Designers love its confidence and its “in-your-face” honesty.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Accordion Item 3 -->
  <div
    class="border-4 border-black rounded-2xl bg-blue-200 shadow-[6px_6px_0_0_#000] cursor-pointer hover:-translate-y-1 active:translate-y-0 duration-150 ease-linear"
    @click="open === 3 ? open = null : open = 3"
  >
    <div
      class="flex justify-between items-center px-6 py-4 font-bold text-black select-none"
    >
      <span>When should I use it?</span>
      <span class="relative flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6">
        <span class="absolute w-4 h-0.5 bg-black"></span>
        <span
          class="absolute h-4 w-0.5 bg-black transition-opacity duration-200"
          :class="open === 3 ? 'opacity-0' : 'opacity-100'"></span>
      </span>
    </div>

    <div
      class="px-6 text-gray-900 text-sm leading-relaxed overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out"
      :class="open === 3 ? 'max-h-40 pb-4' : 'max-h-0 pb-0'"
    >
      Use it for landing pages, documentation, and component showcases where
      personality matters. Let your brand feel playful and bold!
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
